\begin_layout Subsection
Basic Steps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The primary steps in the center localization algorithm include:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Load an input image comprising integral values representing intensity (e.g.
 inGrid) and convert these values to floating point data structure in memory
 (e.g.
 loadGrid).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Produce softGrid by running a smoothing filter with loadGrid as input.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Produce gradGrid by running a gradient filter with softGrid as input.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Create corrEdgels collection by finding gradGrid elements that have corroboratio
n within local neighborhood.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This also results in associating a weight with each corrEdgel (TODO/TBD
 address EdgelInfo collection?)
